social_posts.post_text: Not much better for a car guy than driving the right car, in the right place, at the right time. Wheeled a vintage Alfa Spider from Sorrento to Positano Italy in the rain today and it was something I’ll never forget. Like the perfect bottle of wine during a special occasion, or your favorite cigar with a great friend, today checked all the boxes. #alfa  #alfaromeo #alfaspider #italy #amalfi #sorrento #positano #bucketlist #yolo #instagood #amazingcars #carsofinstagram #amalficoast #napels #hyundai #hyundaiboardofexcellence

Kneeling at the alter of St. Andrew in Amalfi. Some of you know, although most won’t care but my Mother comes from a large Italian/American Catholic Family. I was named after the first Apostle Andrew, Brother of St. Peter. Andrew is buried in this crypt beneath the alter bearing his sculpture with the X shaped cross behind him. I never thought I’d make it here to pay my respects but here I was. Powerful moment for me. #amalfi #christian #catholic #standrew #sorrento #jesus #apostle #positano #italian #cathedral #cathedralstandrew #grateful #christianity

Happy 97th Birthday to this AMAZING lady. I could go on and on about how incredible she is but I’ll start with the key points. She raised 9 children with her Husband Percy who helped put a man on the the moon, space shuttles into space, and the international space station into orbit. She was a Grandmother to 21 grandchildren and I’ve lost count of how many great grandchildren she now has.  She is the Matriarch of our Family and we’re all so blessed to have been gifted her for all these years. She has set the example for our family for multiple generations now.
Happy Birthday Grandma Miglicco!!!!! 👏🏻🙏🏻 #happybirthday #happy #hapiness #greatestgeneration #thegreatestgeneration #grandma #texas #texan #christian #catholic #greatgrandma

social_posts.post_text: I don’t post much about golf (probably because I don’t play as well as I used too), but it was nice to get some competitive rounds in at @miramontcc this week with RW enroute to winning our flight and advancing to the 14 team playoff where we got knocked out after advancing to the round of 7 in their annual Member/Guest Tournament known as The Legacy.  The event was incredibly well run and organized from start to finish. Flights of two man teams, based on combined handicaps, played 5 nine hole four-ball matches to determine the eventual flight winners that would advance to the final 14 team 3 hole knockout rounds.  All great competitive matches with legit handicaps (no bs sandbagging) made for an incredible week at a special place. #collegestation #miramont #miramontcc #bryantx #bryancollegestation #collegestationtx #tx #texas #txgolf #golf #texasgolf #ididntbreakanywindowsthisweekorkillanygeeseoffthetee

So many blessings from 2023 that I’m so grateful and truly thankful for.  1. This first photo was taken February 18th 2023 and I weighed around 267lbs. Most of you that know me outside of IG know that weight is something I’ve struggled with since my teenage years. I’ve yo-yo’d up and down more times than I can count and as defeated as I’ve felt over the years I’ve always told myself that I was never going to quit or give up on finding a way to keep my weight down.  I’m not going to go into all of the details but I’m happy that I’ve found a combination of diet, exercise, meditation that has finally helped me gain control and maintain a much healthier weight without having to go the surgery route.  I’m down 70lbs and in the best shape I’ve been in since 2002. 😳. 2. Really excited to add a Viper to the garage again in 2023! Too many memories and great people/friendships to not be a part of that community in some way.  3. College Station Hyundai being named a 2023 Hyundai Dealer of the Year!  Massively proud of our growing and not so little store in College Station TX. Professionally I couldn’t be happier going into 2024, and look forward to my time on the Regional Dealer Council over these next few years.  4. Watching my Daughters grow so much this year. B and C continue to bless us everyday and make life worth living on a level we never thought was possible.  5. Time spent with family. Great wine was had, stories told, and hugs given. So fortunate to still have so many family members still with us.  6. And to the next chapters with Charlie, Terri, and the girls. It’s going to be fun. 😂. 7. And lastly time spent with friends, wether on the golf course, around a fire pit, or with a cigar and my favorite bourbon, it’s been a great year.
